description.narrative: The development objectives of the Project are: (i) to assist in reducing the commercial losses in the electricity and gas sectors, and to lay the foundation for the improvement of the financial viability of the electricity and gas utilities in a socially responsible manner; and (ii) to assist in the viability assessment of the proposed Rogun HEP in Tajikistan.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :DFA Preamble Section (A) and DFA Section 3.05 | Description :The Govt shall ensure that the Strategy for theDev't of the Energy Sector as depicted in the Letter of Development Strategy dated March 18, 2005 is carried out in a timely andeffective manner. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :DFA Section 3.05 (a) and (b) | Description :The Borrower shall: (a) take all actions on its part to ensure thatall state owned enterprises and budget organizations shall pay in full their electricity and gas obligations to BT and TG... |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :DFA Section 3.06 | Description :The Govt shall not take any actions to modify the legal character, ownership,control, or structure of BT and TG which adversely affect the implementation of the Project w/o prior consent of the Assoc |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :DFA Section 3.08 (a) | Description :Borrower shall cause BT to carry out TEAS & ESIA under Part C of Project perTOR agreed with Association and in compliance with safeguard policies of Asso. Borrower shall:i) fully participate in work ofEngineering, Dam Safety Panel, Env. & Social Panel, in Panel's & riparian consultation mtgs,ii) provide supporting serv to Panelsas agreed with Asso.iii)ensure comments & recomm. in final report | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :DFA Section 3.08 (b) | Description :Borrower shall: i)ensure no reall. of residents from proposed Rogun damfuture reservoir area till Resett. Pol. Framework, Resett. Action Plan and Resett. Audit Rep, satisfactory to Association & ESIA,prepared, ii)make best efforts to avoid reloc. of residents in vicinity of Rogun Dam until docs. in i) prepared, iii) in case ofcontinued resett. Borr.should follow appl. legal & int. practices. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :DFA Section 3.08 (c) | Description :Borrower shall ensure no actions taken which lead or result in diversion ofwaters along Vakhsh River until assessment to coffer dam and 70 m dam facility, as part of TEAS & ESIA completed, and draft rep.shared with Riparian States (RS) and comments received from RS within reasonable time and such assess. reviewed with Panels todetermine feasibility of construc. dam facility within Rogun HEP. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :FA Schedule 2 Section I.A.4 (b) | Description :The Recipient shall take all actions necessary on its part,including but not limited to, tariff increases, and measures to improvecollections from all categories of consumers, to enable theProject Implementing Entity achieve Short-Term Cost Recovery for the year ending 2013 and onwards. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :FA Supplemental Letter dated June 29, 2012 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that activities on theRogun HEP site are limited to maintenance of the existing structures (including essential measures to ensure safety and stabilityof existing works as of June 30, 2012, such as supports, grouting, anchors, and guniting) and studies and investigations asrecommended by the TEAS and ESIA consultants | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :FA Supplemental Letter dated June 29, 2012 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that no further newconstruction or related activities are undertaken unless and until the assessments and consultations referenced in the SectionI.D.3 of the FA have been completed | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :FA Supplemental Letter dated June 29, 2012 | Description :The Recipient will ensure that the Rogun Joint-StockCompany provides monthly progress reports to the Association about the status and scope of activities on the Rogun Project by the10th day of each month (starting from August 10, 2012) | Frequency :Monthly
